0=\lim_{k\to\infty} \mu(B_k)=\lim_{k\to\infty}\left(\mu\left(\bigcup_{i=1}^\infty A_i\right)-\mu\left(\bigcup_{i=1}^k A_i\right)\right)=\mu\left(\bigcup_{i=1}^\infty A_i\right)-\lim_{k\to\infty}\mu\left(\bigcup_{i=1}^k A_i\right),
\mu\left(\bigcup_{i=1}^\infty A_i\right)=\lim_{k\to\infty}\mu\left(\bigcup_{i=1}^k A_i\right)\overset{ii}{=}\lim_{k\to\infty}\sum_{i=1}^k\mu(A_i)=\sum_{i=1}^\infty \mu(A_i)
